{"lemma":"ذ","slug":"ذ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"abbrev","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["character","symbol"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13600"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"character","gloss":"The ninth letter of the Arabic alphabet, called ذَال (ḏāl) and written in the Arabic script; preceded by د (d) and followed by ر (r).","tags":["letter"]},{"pos":"symbol","gloss":"The twenty-fifth numeral symbol of the Arabic alphabet (traditional abjad order, used for list numbering), written in the Arabic script; preceded by خ (ḵ) and followed by ض (ḍ)."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from د (d), and originally written as such (in rasm) by analogy with Nabatean tradition, as Nabatean cognates of Arabic words with /ð/ were indiscriminately spelled using 𐢅 (d)."},"ipa":["/ðaːl/","/ð/","/d/","/z/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13600","headword_ar":"ذ","root":"*","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ninth letter of the alphabet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAlN","text_ar":"ذَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is one of the letters termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majohuwrap","text_ar":"مَجْهُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or vocal, i. e. pronounced with the voice, and not with the breath only]: and of the letters termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"livawiy~ap","text_ar":"لِثَوِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or gingival], which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*","text_ar":"ذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; wherefore it is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaEo*ama","text_ar":"تَلَعْذَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaEovama","text_ar":"تَلَعْثَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it is said to be substituted for the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fa$ar~i*o bihimo","text_ar":"فَشَرِّذْ بِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as some read] in the Kur [viii. 59, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fa$ar~ido bhm","text_ar":"فَشَرِّدْ بهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  [As a numeral, it denotes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seven hundred."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}